18/03/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police on Tuesday (March 17th) arrested 21-year-old imam Ismet Graca in connection with illegal drug dealing. 
Graca is originally from Serbia's region of Sandzak but was an imam in the Bosnian village of Sijenica. 
Police say they arrested him with 2.5kg of heroin, 200g of marijuana, 10g of cocaine and 51 ecstasy pills worth a total of over 120,000 euros. 
They arrested five other people as well. 
(Dnevni Avaz, Vesti, Kurir, Glas Javnosti, 24 Sata, Jutarnji List - 17/03/09)
